<TITLE> Shaikhul Hadith Azizul Haque faces attempted murder charges in lawsuit </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 27 (bdnews24.com) -- Two separate cases have been filed against Khelafat Majlish chairman Shaikhul Hadith Maulana Azizul Haque and party colleague Mufti Shahidul Haque, a police official said Sunday. One Mohammad Ali filed the case with Mohammadpur Police Station, accusing the duo of attempted murder and using explosives, sub-inspector Mohammad Alim told bdnews24.com. Another 13 people have been named in the case, Alim said. According to case details, the plaintiff's father was named as Abdus sattar with his address on Saat Masjid Basila Road in Mohammadpur. Ali in the case said Azizul and Shahidul led a group of 15 on Nov 30, 2001 to attack him at Dhanmondi's Jamia Rahmania Arabia Madrasa. They allegedly threatened to kill him. The group also vandalised the madrasa and charged a small homemade bomb on the day, the plaintiff alleged. bdnews24.
